                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4193: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-15T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 15, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 15—6:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>225. Following from American Consul General at Shanghai: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“February 14, 7 p.m. Following from <persName corresp="#p_MCW1"
                                >Mayer</persName> for Military Attaché: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>[‘]The Japanese unloading nine transports February 15th. Estimate
                                    total Japanese Army here February 15th will be 20,000. Only
                                    light artillery unloaded so far. Believe units to be 9th
                                    Division and balance of 12th part of which has been operating
                                    against Woosung. Japanese land aeroplanes consist of 9 pursuit
                                    and 18 bombers. Woosung Creek crossed and forts should be
                                    captured soon.’ ”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
